# Notification Customization Guide with MagicBell
created: undefined, last updated: 2026-04-08, [Read more](https://www.magicbell.com/blog/notification-customization-with-magicbell)

We make notification customization easy with our MagicBell React SDK and MagicBell Browser/JavaScript Client.
(with support for English, Spanish, and Brazilian Portuguese)!
...
This `Provider` component takes the user JWT token to get the notifications for a user.
...
If you want more control over the notifications, you can get started with the MagicBell JS client, which provides various services:
1. Channels Service
2. Integrations Service
3. Notifications Service
For example, if you want to list all notifications for a user:
```
import { Client } from 'magicbell-js/user-client';
(async () => {
const client = new Client({
token: 'YOUR_TOKEN',
});
const { data } = await client.notifications.listNotifications({
limit: 6,
startingAfter: 'starting_after',
endingBefore: 'ending_before',
status: 'status',
category: 'category',
topic: 'topic',
});
console.log(data);
})();
```
You can use the Notifications Service to:
- Lists notifications.
- Archive notifications.
- Marks notifications as read.
- Gets a notification by ID etc.
You can find more information about NotificationsService here.

